40","1095":"1095","1040":"1040","1150":"1150","Pentney, Norfolk, England":"Pentney, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","Pentney, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Pentney, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","Normandy, France":"Normandy, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert de Vallibus was born in 1095, in Pentney, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom, his father, Robert de Vaux, was 50 and his mother, Ada Deengayne, was 56. He had at least 1 son with Agnes Fitzwalter. He died in 1154, in his hometown, at the age of 59."},"et":{"1095–1154":"1095–1154","1097–1140":"1097–1140","1117–1150":"1117–1150","1045–1095":"1045–1095","1040–1067":"1040–1067","about 1150":"umbes 1150","1117":"1117","about 1117":"umbes 1117","1067":"1067","1045":"1045","1154":"1154","1097":"1097","1140":"1140","1095":"1095","1040":"1040","1150":"1150","Pentney, Norfolk, England":"Pentney, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Pentney, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Pentney, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Normandy, France":"Normandie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1095–1154":"1095–1154","1097–1140":"1097–1140","1117–1150":"1117–1150","1045–1095":"1045–1095","1040–1067":"1040–1067","about 1150":"noin 1150","1117":"1117","about 1117":"noin 1117","1067":"1067","1045":"1045","1154":"1154","1097":"1097","1140":"1140","1095":"1095","1040":"1040","1150":"1150","Pentney, Norfolk, England":"Pentney, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Pentney, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Pentney, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Normandy, France":"Normandie, Ranska"},"fr":{"1095–1154":"1095–1154","1097–1140":"1097–1140","1117–1150":"1117–1150","1045–1095":"1045–1095","1040–1067":"1040–1067","about 1150":"environ 1150","1117":"1117","about 1117":"environ 1117","1067":"1067","1045":"1045","1154":"1154","1097":"1097","1140":"1140","1095":"1095","1040":"1040","1150":"1150","Pentney, Norfolk, England":"Pentney, Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Pentney, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Pentney, Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Normandy, France":"Normandie, Fr